item.title: Bike Map
item.description: OSM data served from PostGIS. Queried the database to select and symbolize features. Map shows bike routes of various types along with selected amenities. Topography and hydrography from the Puget Sound LIDAR Consortium and the US Geological Survey. Building outlines from OSM.

item.title: Canvass Maps
item.description: Example walk map produced for political campaigns. Shaded and numbered parcels indicate the locations of targeted voters. This format is an efficient way of orienting volunteers and communicating exactly where they need to go.

item.title: Middlefork Map
item.description: Detail from map of the area around the Middlefork Snoqualmie valley in east King County, Washington.

item.title: San Juan Islands Map
item.description: Built in QGIS with data from NOAA, US Department of Agricutlure, San Juan County, Whatcom County, and Skagit County

item.title: Turnout Visualization
item.description: A plot of the distributions of about 70,000 measurements of voter turnout by precinct for 28 elections in King County, WA. Queried from an election results table containing 13,000,000 rows. Countywide mesaurements are symbolized in black, while measurements from precincts within the City of Seattle are symbolized in gray.

item.title: Voter's Edge
item.description: Was responsible for the contents of the backend databases used to provide address-customized ballots to millions of users of VotersEdge.org, a popular online voter guide application.
